listing_desc.1: Our market is managed by the City of Bloomington's Economic & Community Development Department. Everything you buy from our farmers, artists, and prepared food artisans is produced by them. There is a variety of organic and chemical-free produce. It's all fresh, original, and guaranteed to come from your own community.
listing_desc.3: The Galesburg Farmers' Market is your one-stop-shop for all the local goods you need, from fresh fruits and veggies, meats and eggs, honey, baked goods and prepared foods, handmade crafts and jewelry, and so much more. Find us in downtown Galesburg near the corner of Simmons and Seminary every Saturday from 8-12, May through October.
listing_desc.31: We have Artisan breads, candy , canned goods, crafts, and baked goods
listing_desc.339: We are the oldest farmers market in Lake County, Illinois.  We are a traditional farmers market that only sells food products grown or made by the vendor, and we have great vendors with a very wide variety of products.
